  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onions and garlic; sauté for about 3 minutes until fragrant.",
    "Add bell pepper to the skillet; stir-fry for an additional 5-7 minutes or until softened.",
    "Add ground lamb, season with salt and pepper, and cook until browned on all sides. Deglaze with lemon juice and continue cooking.",
    "Gradually add honey to the skillet, stirring constantly to prevent clumping and ensure a smooth texture. Cook for about 2-3 minutes or until thickened.",
    "Remove from heat; stir in chopped parsley if using."
